# 4 main files -so far-:


# core_engine.py -> World structure & game loop

# entities.p -> Characters, NPCs, bosses (ECS (Entity Component System) pattern -> an approach for game development)

# systems.py -> Combat, inventory, travel, quests, AI)

# world_setup.py -> Content creation (biomes, bosses, NPCs)

# main.py -> Game execution & player interaction


"""
FILE 1: core_engine.py - The foundation
Defines the core game structure - how the world exists and updates

KEY CLASSES:

1. Game Class
OOP Concept: Encapsulation - internal game state is hidden, controlled through methods.

2. World Class
OOP Concept: Composition - World is made up of many smalles objects (biomes, entities).

3. Biome Class
OOP Concept: Aggregation - Biomes contain entities but they don't own them.

4. WorldRules & EventSystem Classes
OOP Concept: Single Responsibility Principle - each class has one clear purpose.
"""


"""
FILE 2: entities.py - The Entity-Component System
Implements a flexible, modular character system where entities are built from reusable components.

KEY CLASSES:

1. Component (Base Class)
OOP Concept: Abstraction & Inheritance - child components inherit and override methods.

2. Concrete Components (Inheritance)
OOP Concept: Composition over Inheritance - can mix and match components to create diverse entities.

3. BaseEntity Class
OOP Concept: Polymorphism - different entities can be treated uniformly through a common interface.

4. Specialized Entities (Inheritance)
OOP Concept: Inheritance - specialized entities extend base functionality while reusing common code.

5. BossAIComponent (Polymorphism example)
OOP Concept: Inherits from AIcomponent, overrides behavior for bosses.
"""


"""
FILE 3: systems.py - The Game Mechanics
Implements game logic that operates on entities and components.

KEY CLASSES:

1. GameSystem (Base Class)
OOP Concept: Interface Pattern - ensures all systems have consistent update() method.

2. EventSystem
OOP Concept: Inheritance - inherits from GameSystem, adds event-specific logic.

3. CombatSystem
OOP Concept: Encapsulation - all combat logic in one class.

4. InventorySystem
OOP Concept: Single Responsibility Principle - manages only inventory-related tasks.

5. QuestSystem + Quest Class
OOP Concept: Callback Pattern - quests can trigger actions when completed.

6. AIController
OOP Concept: Strategy Pattern - each AI can implement different logic.
"""


"""
FILE 4: world_setup.py - Content Creation
Instantiates all game content (biomes, bosses, NPCs)

KEY FUNCTION:

def build_world() -> World

OOP Concept: Factory Pattern - separates content from game logic.
"""


"""
FILE 5: main.py - Game Loop
Ties everything together, handles player input and runs the game.

KEY COMPONENTS:

1. Initialization
OOP Concept: Dependency Injection - systems receive 'world' as parameter; makes testing easier

2. Main Loop
OOP Concept: Game Loop Pattern - continuously updates the game state.
"""

